  "panels": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "title": "Server Health — Self-Hosted Only",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 6,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "\nStorage layer + server process health. **Self-hosted only, permanently** — Temporal Cloud manages\npersistence and the server process itself, and does not expose either to customers on any\ntopology. Consolidated here from what used to be three near-identical \"Persistence Latency\"\npanels duplicated across the Critical Flows dashboards (Overview, Flow 1, Flow 2) — one copy,\nsince the query doesn't change per flow.\n\nFor the request-path metrics that DO work on both Cloud and self-hosted (RPS/errors/latency by\noperation, availability), see the **Temporal Critical Flows** folder instead.\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "row",
      "title": "Persistence",
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 6
      },
      "id": 2,
      "panels": []
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Persistence RPS by Operation",
      "description": "On Postgres the storage hot-path collapses to the persistence API layer.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "prometheus-kind"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 7
      },
      "id": 3,
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "reqps",
          "custom": {
            "drawStyle": "line",
            "fillOpacity": 10,
            "showPoints": "never"
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "displayMode": "list",
          "placement": "bottom"
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi",
          "sort": "desc"
        }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "prometheus-kind"
          },
          "expr": "sum by (operation) (rate(persistence_requests{operation=~\"CreateWorkflowExecution|UpdateWorkflowExecution|CreateWorkflowExecutionTasks|.*\"}[$rate]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{operation}}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Persistence Latency p99 by Operation",
      "description": "On Postgres the storage hot-path collapses to the persistence API layer.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "prometheus-kind"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 12,
        "y": 7
      },
      "id": 4,
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "s",
          "custom": {
            "drawStyle": "line",
            "fillOpacity": 10,
            "showPoints": "never"
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "displayMode": "list",
          "placement": "bottom"
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi",
          "sort": "desc"
        }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "prometheus-kind"
          },
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.99, sum by (operation, le) (rate(persistence_latency_bucket[$rate])))",
          "legendFormat": "{{operation}}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "row",
      "title": "Process Health",
